Definition at line 213 of file PageInfo.h.

enum gaia::core::PageInfo::PAGE_FLAG_MASK

Page flage mask.

Enumerator:
FLAG_MULTIPROCESS 

Bit in return value of getFlagMask() indicating whether this page is able to run in multiple processes.

If true, the system may instantiate it in the some process as the process starting it in order to conserve resources. If false, the default, it always runs in getProcessName().

FLAG_FINISH_ON_TASK_LAUNCH 

Bit in return value of getFlagMask() indicating that, when the page's task is relaunched from home, this page should be finished.

FLAG_CLEAR_TASK_ON_LAUNCH 

Bit in return value of getFlagMask() indicating that, when the page is the root of a task, that task's stack should be cleared each time the user re-launches it from home.

As a result, the user will always return to the original page at the top of the task. This flag only applies to pages that are used to start the root of a new task.

FLAG_ALWAYS_RETAIN_TASK_STATE 

Bit in return value of getFlagMask() indicating that, when the page is the root of a task, that task's stack should never be cleared when it is relaunched from home.

FLAG_STATE_NOT_NEEDED 

Bit in return value of getFlagMask() indicating that the page's state is not required to be saved, so that if there is a failure the page will not be removed from the page stack.

FLAG_EXCLUDE_FROM_RECENTS 

Bit in return value of getFlagMask() that indicates that the page should not appear in the list of recently launched pages.

FLAG_ALLOW_TASK_REPARENTING 

Bit in return value of getFlagMask() that indicates that the page can be moved between tasks based on its task affinity.

FLAG_NO_HISTORY 

Bit in return value of getFlagMask() indicating that, when the user navigates away from an page, it should be finished.

FLAG_FINISH_ON_CLOSE_SYSTEM_DIALOGS 

Bit in return value of getFlagMask indicating that, when a request to close system windows happens, this page is finished.

int32_t gaia::core::PageInfo::getConfigChangesMask ( ) const

Bit mask of kinds of configuration changes that this page can handle itself (without being restarted by the system).

Contains any combination of: CONFIG_FONT_SCALE, CONFIG_KEYBOARD, CONFIG_LOCALE, CONFIG_MCC, CONFIG_MNC, CONFIG_NAVIGATION, CONFIG_ORIENTATION, CONFIG_SCREEN_LAYOUT, CONFIG_TOUCHSCREEN, CONFIG_UI_MODE.

Returns:
the mask indicate what kind of changes can this page can handle.
